items.body:
Hello!

There is currently a bug with the `MultiSelect` component, when **not filterable**.

This can be reproduced in storybook here: https://react.carbondesignsystem.com/?path=/story/components-multiselect--default

If you open the multiselect and begin typing (note: difficult in storybook due to shortcut commands), an error occurs.
```Uncaught TypeError: items.map is not a function```

The error relates to this code:
```
var _useSelect = (0, _downshift.useSelect)((0, _createPropAdapter.mapDownshiftProps)(_objectSpread(_objectSpread({}, downshiftProps), {}, {
    highlightedIndex: highlightedIndex,
    isOpen: isOpen,
    itemToString: function itemToString(items) {
      return Array.isArray(items) && items.map(function (item) {
        return _itemToString(item);
      }).join(', ') || '';
    },
    onStateChange: onStateChange,
    selectedItem: controlledSelectedItems,
    items: items
  }))),
```

The itemToString part fails due to `items` not being an array. Currently patching with the following:
```
return Array.isArray(items) && items.map(function (item) {
        return _itemToString(item);
      }).join(', ') || '';
```

One solution might be to remove the event listener from the Select when not filterable, unless there are keys used for opening/closing the menu in which case maybe more specific key down events.
